# Project
This repository is a monorepo for a stock platform with:
- datalake service (system of record)
- MCP service for OpenClaw/agent use
- SaaS/API gateway
- analytics service
- screener service
- later a web UX layer

# Architecture rules
- Keep business logic in services, not route handlers.
- Keep storage access behind repository interfaces.
- Do not duplicate domain logic between datalake, API, and MCP services.
- MCP tools must call existing service-layer methods.
- OpenClaw skills should contain guidance, not business logic.
- Postgres is the initial system of record.
- Keep the data model and repositories migration-friendly to TimescaleDB later.
- DuckDB is for analytics and exports, not the primary write store.

# Data rules
- One canonical row per (ticker_id, trading_date).
- All writes of daily bars must be idempotent upserts.
- Missed-day backfills must work automatically.
- Preserve raw and adjusted Tiingo fields.
- Never spread provider-specific field names across the codebase; map them once.

# Quality rules
- Write tests with every feature.
- Every PR-sized task should include unit tests.
- Persistence or contract changes require integration tests.
- User-facing workflows require E2E tests.
- Prefer explicit typing and small files.